Guild "A" decides to head to North Wing in ToV and attempt to kill Aaryonar, 7 day spawn. they have 60 people in the zone ready to kill the mighty dragon, their first attempt, they manage to get his health to read Ar| SO CLOSE! but wait! some members of Guild "B" are starting to arrive in ToV, in about 15 minutes time, 35 members of Guild "B" are in the zone and at Aryonar's spot! 40 members of Guild "A" in zone now starting their ressing and rebuffing, <br>
<br>
Option 1.)<br>
Guild "B" pulls the mighty dragon after having much experience in killing it while Guild "A" is being ressed in and dying instantly to the AE from Aryonar. Guild "B" then moves past the crippled guild and continues to kill other dragons in north wing.<br>
<br>
Option 2.)<br>
15 members of Guild "B" decide to stay while the rest leave and offer to help Guild "A" which would be 75 people in the zone to kill mobs that don't require more than 30-40, strategies are shared between the guild, Guild "A" learns everything from experienced people without figuring it out themselves, and major conflicts between who gets what loot from which guild.<br>
<br>
Option 3.)<br>
Guild "B" leaves, Guild "A" tries again, if Guild "A" should happen to fail continuously and finally throw in the towel, they notify Guild "B: that they are now leaving and free to move in.<br>
<br>
Now, option 1 is what KC decided to do to GoTK, option 2, which is Trewayn's suggestion,  can work, but it hurts both guilds, I'm sure many people in the stronger guild would not like their secrets and strategies released to others.. option 3 is what should have happened, and what normally happens between respectable guilds.. not to mention.. common sense. come on people!<br>
<br>
<br>
The Asshole has spoken.<br>
